==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nontechnical
<hw>nontechnical</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>not
characteristic of or skilled in applied arts and sciences; <as>as,
<ex>nontechnical</ex> aspects of the job; <ex>nontechnical</ex>
training</as>. Opposite of <ant>technical</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> untechnical.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>comprehensible to the general public; not requiring
specialized training to be understood; <as>as, written for the popular
press in plain <ex>nontechnical</ex> language</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lay, plain, popular, unspecialized,
untechnical.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nontelescoping</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>nontelescopic</ent>⟦br⟧
